author: Jason Brennan
title: Live Rugby World Cup 2015
text:
All of the details for today's games below:
11.30am: Pool C: Argentina v Namibia
Kick-Off: 12.00pm
Stadium: Leicester City Stadium
While unlikely, Argentina can still slip up and fail to make the quarter-final, but that'd be an even bigger shock than Japan's victory over the Springboks, seeing as the Pumas have looked very strong in their opening three games, and Namibia have only managed to pick up a losing bonus point. We're expecting tries, and plenty of them.
2.00pm: Pool D: Italy v Romania
Kick-Off: 2.30pm
Stadium: Sandy Park
These two sides have nothing to play for apart from pride, and a third place finish, which is all they can hope for having failed to pick up a scalp against the groups two bigger sides, Ireland and France. Judging from both sides attacking play so far in the tournament we might not see champagne football, but we've seen enough of them to know they'll be giving it their all.
4.30pm: Pool D: Ireland v France
Kick-Off: 4.45pm
Stadium: Millennium Stadium
The big one. The one we've all been waiting for. We're not going to jinx it by predicting a result, actually, we won't talk about anything just in case, we're superstitious like that. What we will say is we couldn't care about the performance, we just want to pick up the W and move on to a quarter-final with Argentina. Lets not talk about what'll happen is we lose. C'mon lads, get'r'done!
